Here we need n/3 more numbers, means 2 CANDIDATES
2 Method can be there of O(NLOGN) AND O(N)

MAP METHOD--> 
What is the question?

Given:nums = [1,2,1,1,3,2]

Length:n = 6

Threshold-n/3 = 2
We need elements appearing more than 2 times.
Frequency:
1 -> 3
2 -> 2
3 -> 1
Answer:[1] because only 1 appears more than 2 times.

SO, 

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> majorityElementTwo(vector<int>& nums) {

        map<int, int> frequency;

        for(int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++)
        {
            frequency[nums[i]]++;
        }

        vector<int> answer;

        int requiredFrequency = nums.size() / 3;

        for(auto entry : frequency)   //entry means the values in the map of first and second stored EXAMPLE- entry.first  = 1 entry.second = 3
        {
            if(entry.second > requiredFrequency)    //second entry is the frequecy entry and if greater thna the required one 
            {
                answer.push_back(entry.first);   //we push the value, and the entry.first is the value of number in the array
            }
        }

        return answer;
    }
};
